cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper deals with facial point tracking in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an incremental learning approach, which involves updating the model on the fly, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a deep neural network for evaluating fitting results also suggests relevance to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed method, which could be of interest to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) community.
